==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Titular
<hw>Tit"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>titulaire</ets>, fr. L. <ets>titulus</ets>. See
<er>Title</er>.]</ety> <def>Existing in title or name only; nominal;
having the title to an office or dignity without discharging its
appropriate duties; <as>as, a <ex>titular</ex> prince</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If these magnificent titles yet remain⟦br⟧
Not merely <qex>titular</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Titular bishop</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Bishop</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Titular</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Titular
<hw>Tit"u*lar</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A titulary.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Titularity</ent>⟦br⟧
